CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1782319683
OL,3,CTwo-thirds of surveyed Channel
OL,4,CIslanders want UK's under-16s social
OL,5,Cmedia ban
OL,7,FTwo-thirds of people surveyed in the
OL,8,FChannel Islands believe social media
OL,9,Fshould be banned for under-16s.
OL,11,FThe survey from Island Global Research
OL,12,Fasked residents from Jersey, Guernsey,
OL,13,Fthe Isle of Man, and Gibraltar whether
OL,14,Fa social media ban for under-16s
OL,15,Fshould be introduced for their
OL,16,Frespective territories.
OL,18,FIt comes after the UK Government
OL,19,Fannounced plans to impose the
OL,20,Frestriction by early 2027.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,354,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1782319683
OL,3,CTwo-thirds of surveyed Channel
OL,4,CIslanders want UK's under-16s social
OL,5,Cmedia ban
OL,7,FAlmost 1,700 people in Jersey and
OL,8,FGuernsey over the age of 16 were
OL,9,Fsurveyed between 17 and 22 June 2026,
OL,10,Fwith the overall majority being
OL,11,Fsupportive of the scheme being
OL,12,Fintroduced in the Bailiwicks.
OL,14,FIt concluded that there was
OL,15,F"widespread agreement" that social
OL,16,Fmedia was a problem, but there was
OL,17,Fdivided opinion on whether parents,
OL,18,Fgovernment, or tech companies should
OL,19,Fbe responsible for providing a
OL,20,Fsolution.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,354,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1782319683
OL,3,CTwo-thirds of surveyed Channel
OL,4,CIslanders want UK's under-16s social
OL,5,Cmedia ban
OL,7,FRespondents who supported a social
OL,8,Fmedia ban were concerned about
OL,9,Fprotecting children, addiction, and
OL,10,Fdevelopmental problems.
OL,12,FRespondents who answered 'Yes' to the
OL,13,Fquestion 'Do you think the survey
OL,14,Fsocial media ban for under 16s ` using
OL,15,Fthe same model as the UK and Australia
OL,16,F` should be introduced in your island?'
OL,18,FThose who voted 'Yes' had strong
OL,19,Fcriticisms that social media platforms
OL,20,Ffail to protect users and are
OL,21,Funwilling to self-regulate.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,354,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1782319683
OL,3,CTwo-thirds of surveyed Channel
OL,4,CIslanders want UK's under-16s social
OL,5,Cmedia ban
OL,7,FThere were also concerns that children
OL,8,Fwere "welded to phones" and that
OL,9,Fplatforms are designed to be highly
OL,10,Faddictive, encouraging "doom
OL,11,Fscrolling".
OL,13,FOnly 23% of respondents in Jersey
OL,14,Fanswered 'No', with 5% saying they
OL,15,Fwere unsure; in Guernsey, 30% answered
OL,16,F'No' and 7% were unsure.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
